23: Subject: CVE-2014-4877: Arbitrary Symlink Access
25: Wget was susceptible to a symlink attack which could create arbitrary
26: files, directories or symbolic links and set their permissions when
27: retrieving a directory recursively through FTP. This commit changes the
28: default settings in Wget such that Wget no longer creates local symbolic
29: links, but rather traverses them and retrieves the pointed-to file in
30: such a retrieval.
32: The old behaviour can be attained by passing the --retr-symlinks=no
33: option to the Wget invokation command.
35: -- Thorsten Alteholz <debian@alteholz.de>  Wed, 29 Oct 2014 19:00:14 +0100

1: The old behaviour can be attained by passing the --retr-symlinks=no
